105.3	War_of_Currents	War of Currents	In the "War of Currents" era (sometimes, "War of the Currents" or "Battle of Currents") in the late 1880s, George Westinghouse and Thomas Edison became adversaries due to Edison's promotion of direct current (DC) for electric power distribution over alternating current (AC) advocated by several European companies and Westinghouse Electric based out of Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/ba/Edison.jpg/220px-Edison.jpg
